## Technical Design

### Data Flow

**Field Definitions (Settings Store):**
```
Settings Store
  ├─ customFieldDefinitions
  │   ├─ tasks: FieldDefinition[]
  │   └─ notes: FieldDefinition[]
  └─ Actions
      ├─ addFieldDefinition(target, definition)
      ├─ updateFieldDefinition(target, id, changes)
      └─ deleteFieldDefinition(target, id)
```

**Field Values (Task/Note Stores):**
```
Task/Note Object
  ├─ ...existing fields
  └─ customFields: {
      [fieldId]: value,
      [fieldId]: value,
      ...
  }
```

### Field Type Validation

```typescript
function validateFieldValue(field: FieldDefinition, value: any): boolean {
  switch (field.type) {
    case 'text':
      return typeof value === 'string';
    case 'number':
      return typeof value === 'number' && !isNaN(value);
    case 'date':
      return value instanceof Date || typeof value === 'string'; // ISO string
    case 'select':
      return field.options?.includes(value) ?? false;
    case 'checkbox':
      return typeof value === 'boolean';
    default:
      return false;
  }
}
```

### Migration Strategy

**Backward Compatibility:**
- customFields is optional (`customFields?: CustomFieldsMap`)
- Existing tasks/notes without customFields continue to work
- No migration needed

**Forward Migration:**
- When user creates first field definition, initialize empty customFields: {}
- When field definition deleted, remove values from all tasks/notes (optional cleanup)

